args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the Northern Negotiators event.
E-everyone here looks so...fancy.\nIt's just how I'd imagined a royal\nbanquet would be!
Say, Joachim? What do you do at events\nlike this? It's my first time, and I don't\nknow what any of the rules...
Such modesty—yet you managed to sweet-\ntalk Chelle, of all people. Tell me, lad,\nwhat WAS your trick? I must know!
Oof! Oh, I beg your pardon, madam!
Joachim? Oh, drat. I lost him again.
Aw jeez... J-Joachiiim? Where are you?
H-huh? How did I end up out here?
Julia, my turtledove! At long last!
Oh, Remuel! How I've burned to see you!
(Eeep! Oh gosh, is this a lover's tryst?\nI mean, I've read about them in romance\nnovels, but never actually...seen one.)
(They're clearly nobles based on how\nthey're dressed, so I guess they snuck out\nof the banquet?)

You don't know how I've pined for this day
to come, my sweet. I knew we were both
slated to attend tonight's banquet, and
here we are together at last!

Ah, but I do know—for I have pined for it
just as long! Oh, WHY must our fathers
persist in their silly grudge?! Why must
our families hate each other so?!
If they would only accept our union,\nwe could spend every night locked\nin each other's arms!
(I guess their families don't like them\nbeing together, which explains the\nsecret meeting.)
(Oh gosh, Noelle, stop spying on them!\n...Good luck, you two! I hope everything\nworks out!)
(Eeep! Someone ELSE is coming!\nBetter stay hidden right here...)
There you are, Julia my dear!\nI've been searching high and low for...
Fie, but I know the man with you!\nHe's the son of that detestable snake!
I don't care WHOSE son he is!\nRemuel and I are in LOVE!
Poppycock! I won't hear another word of it!\nNo daughter of mine will consort with the\nspawn of that viper! Now come.
So THIS is where you've gotten off to,\nRemuel. Goodness, what is all of this\nabsurd shouting abou...
I say, what are you doing with this\nslavering hyena and his cur daughter?!
Better a hyena than a pathetic\ncarrion jackal such as yourself!
I'm suddenly overtaken with a wave of\nnausea. Julia, come along this instant!
For once, we're in agreement. Remuel!
Some kind of brooch? That poor woman\nmust have dropped it.
I should get it back to her. She's probably\nover in that building where her father\ndragged her off to...
Found her! Um, m-ma'am?\nExcuse me, ma'am?
Hm? Can I help you with something?
BROOCH! Er, I mean, um...this is yours\nhere please take it I'm really sorry!
Goodness, it IS mine! Thank you so much.\nWhere in the world did I drop it?
O-outside... It probably fell off after you\nwere, um...dragged away.
It wasn't my intention to blame you;\nthough I would consider it a great kindness\nif you kept the matter to yourself.
I appreciate it, Miss... Hmm.\nI don't think we've actually met.
I know most every face in Chanzelia,\nyet I've never seen yours before.\nAre you a visitor from elsewhere?
Y-yes, ma'am. My name is Noelle, and I...\nI'm part of the diplomatic contingent\nfrom Svenitla.
You're with that military from up north?\nOh, I've heard some wonderful tales\nof your brave exploits!
Impressive work recently, by the way:\nSecuring a deal out of Chelle\nis no mean feat.
Oh, J-Joachim is the impressive one.\nHe, um...did all the important stuff.
All I did was run around and deliver\norders. S-same as always, really...
But don't high-ranking officers usually give\norders? Forgive me if I'm overstepping;\nI'm largely ignorant of military affairs.
Oh, I don't come up with the orders!\nI'm just a messenger. My job is to deliver\nletters without being caught, basically.
Well, that sounds very important indeed.\nAnd also very brave, to be sneaking past\nan enemy to deliver...
Ah! I am struck with a flash of inspiration!
Let's continue this conversation outside,\nshall we? It wouldn't do to be overheard.
We should have a bit of privacy here.
Noelle, I need your help to deliver this\nlove letter to my beloved Remuel.
Yes. Seeing as how you're an expert in\ndelivering letters in secret, I trust you can\nfind a way to secure this into his care?
You saw for yourself earlier how our\nfathers' inane feud is standing in the way\nof our true love.
If we can't meet in person, then I must\nat least share the contents of my heart\nwith him by way of the pen!
A-all right! I'll make sure your feelings\nreach him one way or the other!
Connecting one person to another\nis a messenger's job, after all!
